      <section eId="sec_1399_O_2">
        <num>1399-O-2</num>
        <heading>Smoking restrictions; certain outdoor areas</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_1399_O_2__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>public parks, beaches, pools, boardwalks, marinas, playgrounds,\nrecreation centers, and group camps; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1399_O_2__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>equipment, buildings and facilities now or hereafter under the\njurisdiction, charge or control of any state or local government agency\nor department that are located at or on any property described in\nparagraph</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1399_O_2__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of this subdivision; provided, however, that for the\npurposes of this section the term public park shall not include the\nAdirondack park or the Catskill park as those terms are defined in\nsection 9-0101 of the environmental conservation law.\n  3. The provisions of this section shall not apply to:</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1399_O_2__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the\nsidewalks immediately adjoining parks, squares and public places;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1399_O_2__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>\nany pedestrian route through any park strip, median or mall that is\nadjacent to vehicular traffic;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1399_O_2__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>parking lots or roadways;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1399_O_2__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>\ntheatrical productions; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1399_O_2__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>any portion of a park that is not used\nfor park purposes, except when smoking has been specifically prohibited\nin a state park or portion thereof by the office of parks, recreation\nand historic preservation. This subdivision shall not limit the\napplicability of any other laws to such places.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
